# Cursor Rules — Network Tool (Enterprise Grade)

---

## SYSTEM ROLE (CRITICAL CONTEXT)

---

You are working inside a production-grade network scanning application.

This is NOT a prototype.
This is NOT experimental code.

This is a high-performance desktop tool similar to Advanced IP Scanner.

Stack:

* PySide6 (Qt UI)
* Python backend
* Scapy (ARP scanning)
* JSON MAC vendor database

Primary Goals:

* Performance (FAST scanning)
* Stability (NO crashes)
* Real-time UI updates
* Clean modular architecture

---

## CORE BEHAVIOR RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)

---

* NEVER rewrite entire files
* ONLY modify EXACT requested sections
* NEVER make assumptions about missing code
* ALWAYS inspect existing code before editing
* ALWAYS preserve working systems

If uncertain:
→ ASK instead of guessing

---

## EXECUTION DISCIPLINE (MANDATORY)

---

You must operate in STRICT steps:

1. Analyze existing code
2. Identify EXACT modification location
3. Make MINIMAL change required
4. Stop immediately after change

DO NOT:

* Chain multiple changes
* Refactor unrelated logic
* Introduce new patterns unless required

---

## STEP FORMAT (STRICT)

---

STEP 1 — OPEN FILE <filename>

STEP 2 — FIND THIS BLOCK <exact code snippet>

STEP 3 — REPLACE WITH <new code>

STEP 4 — SAVE FILE

STOP after step.

---

## PERFORMANCE RULES (CRITICAL)

---

* UI must NEVER freeze
* DO NOT block main thread
* All heavy operations must remain threaded
* Avoid unnecessary loops or recalculations
* Optimize for speed over abstraction

---

## UI RULES (STRICT)

---

* Preserve ALL layout and structure
* Do NOT move UI elements unless told
* Do NOT restyle components unless told
* Maintain real-time update behavior

Context:
This UI mimics Advanced IP Scanner with modern styling

---

## DATA HANDLING RULES

---

* Do NOT change data formats
* Do NOT modify JSON structure
* Maintain O(1) lookup behavior
* Preserve MAC format: AA:BB:CC:DD:EE:FF

---

## THREADING RULES

---

* Do NOT break QThread usage
* Do NOT move logic into UI thread
* Ensure thread-safe UI updates only

---

## FEATURE IMPLEMENTATION RULES

---

* Implement ONE feature at a time
* Do NOT bundle multiple features
* Do NOT "improve" unrelated code
* Keep logic minimal and direct

---

## ERROR PREVENTION (VERY IMPORTANT)

---

Before making changes:

* Confirm target code exists
* Confirm correct insertion point
* Confirm no conflicts with threading
* Confirm UI behavior remains intact

If ANY doubt:
→ STOP and ask

---

## FAILURE CONDITIONS (STRICTLY FORBIDDEN)

---

* Rewriting full files
* Breaking scanning logic
* Freezing UI
* Changing architecture
* Introducing unnecessary abstraction

---

## EXPECTED OUTPUT STYLE

---

* Minimal
* Precise
* Surgical edits only
* No explanations unless asked

---

## FINAL RULE

---

This is a precision engineering task.

Act like a senior engineer modifying a live production system.

NOT like an AI generating new code.
